{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"624aaaca-8371-48fa-abd2-74c1fd49a214","content":"Yes, you **will** hit a compatibility issue. **MSTest v4 dropped support for `net6.0` and `net7.0`** — it only supports `net8.0+`, `net462`, and `uap10.0`.\n\nYour project targets `net6.0`, so upgrading MSTest from 3.8.0 to 4.x will fail to build.\n\n**You have two options:**\n\n1. **Retarget to `net8.0`** (recommended) — update `<TargetFramework>` in your `.csproj`, then upgrade MSTest.\n2. **Stay on MSTest v3** — if you must keep `net6.0`, you cannot use MSTest v4.\n\nWould you like me to retarget to `net8.0` and perform the MSTest v4 upgrade?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"93052303-9d28-46f4-98fe-c256a54bdd46","outputTokens":198},"id":"a715f358-40d9-4483-9513-9bde05bc2b67","timestamp":"2026-04-05T01:02:04.761Z","parentId":"f2cc8aa5-e0bc-4d7a-9d27-b90cd0a853a3"}
